 To celebrate a birthday, one must present a gift and verbal greeting. However, one must first determine the year in question. If the year is the same, then the same gift can be presented, and if the same gift was given, then the same verbal greeting can be given. If the year is not the same, a different gift is necessarily required. This requires that one have the necessary technical knowledge to discern whether a gift is appropriate for a particular age, and one might have to employ
